---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import storyBg from "../assets/farm/cattle-grazing.jpg";
---

<section id="story" class="py-20 md:py-32 relative overflow-hidden bg-white">
  <!-- Background photo -->
  <Image
    src={storyBg}
    alt=""
    class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    widths={[1200, 1920, 2400]}
    sizes="100vw"
    aria-hidden="true"
  />
  <!-- Cream overlay so text stays readable while the photo shows through -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-white/55 via-white/45 to-white/65 pointer-events-none"></div>
  <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-0 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-gold/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 relative">
    <div class="reveal text-center mb-12 md:mb-16">
      <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold mb-3">Our Story</div>
      <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-[clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3.5rem)] tracking-tight text-pasture leading-[1.05]">
        It started in 1996.<br />By accident.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal space-y-6 text-[18px] md:text-[19px] text-ink-muted leading-[1.7] font-normal">
      <p>
        Our family wasn't trying to build anything special back then. We had a small herd of cattle behind the main fields — kept partly on crop residue, partly on store-bought feed when we could afford it. The cattle were insurance. Something you sold when things went wrong.
      </p>
      <p>That year, things went wrong slowly.</p>
      <p>
        Feed prices crept up week by week until buying a sack felt like pouring money into a hole. So we made a choice that felt, at the time, like giving up: we stopped buying feed. We pushed the cattle out to graze on whatever grass grew thick beyond the cultivated land.
      </p>
      <p>We expected losses. Thin animals. Slow growth.</p>
      <p>It didn't happen.</p>

      <blockquote class="font-display text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.25rem)] leading-snug text-pasture italic border-l-4 border-gold pl-6 md:pl-8 my-10 not-italic">
        "The pasture carried more than anyone expected. The cattle stayed healthy. They didn't fatten fast — they fattened <em class="text-gold not-italic">right</em>."
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        And when we finally took one to the butcher, he hesitated. Not because the meat was bad. Because it was different. Leaner. Darker. Held its shape. The next time, he asked for another one.
      </p>
      <p class="font-semibold text-ink">That was thirty years ago. We never went back.</p>
      <p>
        Today, <strong class="text-pasture">Coopers Grass Fed Beef</strong> is still a family operation. Same land. Same approach. Fewer cattle than the big herders, raised longer, on grass alone. We didn't invent grass-fed. We just never stopped.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
